    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02864.001related_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Boston</name>
                    <name type="place">20 Hancock St.</name>
                    <date when="1871-05-16">May 16.</date> 
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Sir:</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>At the suggestion of Mr. Eldridge<ptr target="n0210"/> I enclose a likeness 
                of Father Taylor;<ptr target="n0620"/> having no photo that is as good.</p>
            <p>He died, April 6, 1871, just as the tide turned, going out with the ebb, as 
                an old salt should.</p>

            <closer>
                <salute>Very Truly</salute>
                <signed>Thomas Russell</signed>
                <address>
                    <addrLine>Walt Whitman</addrLine>
                </address>
            </closer>
